data.enText: final; not able to be changed
data.chText: 最后的；决定性的；不可更改的
最后的协议 / 答复 / 声明

data.enText: The definitive version of the text is ready to be published.
data.chText: 正式的文本很快就要发表了。

data.enText: considered to be the best of its kind and almost impossible to improve

data.chText: 最完整可靠的爱因斯坦传记

tr: supplying or being a final or conclusive settlement
example: a determinate answer to the problem
the plain and unequivocal language of the laws"- R.B.Tane

example.ex: No one has come up with a definitive answer as to why this should be so...
example.tran: 对于为什么应该是这样，还没有人想出最终确定的答案。

example.ex: There is no definitive test as yet for the condition.
example.tran: 对这种病目前还没有决定性的检测手段。

value.def: Something that is definitive provides a firm conclusion that cannot be questioned.
value.tran: 明确的;最终的;不可更改的;决定性的

example.ex: The Constitution did not definitively rule out divorce.
example.tran: 宪法没有明确排除离婚。

example.ex: His 'An Orkney Tapestry' is still the definitive book on the islands.
example.tran: 他的《奥克尼挂毯》一书仍是关于这些岛屿的最权威著作。

value.def: A definitive book or performance is thought to be the best of its kind that has ever been done or that will ever be done.
value.tran: （书籍或表演）最佳的，最具权威的
